{
  "texts": [
    "LGBTQ-related tweets are the most likely to express solidarity with a movement.",
    "While we identify systematic differences across issues, we do not explore the mechanisms underlying these patterns.",
    "While it is possible that there are inherent aspects to each issue that contribute to differences in core framing task usage, it is also possible that such variation is due to messages from different issue areas focusing on different types of events and activities.",
    "Relative to tweets with a neutral/unclear stance, tweets with either progressive or conservative stances are much more likely to engage with any core framing task.",
    "Conservative tweets are slightly more likely to contain diagnostic framing than progressive tweets (9.8% vs. 8.5% increase in probability relative to neutral tweets), and particularly the blame frame element."
  ]
}